{"word":"κρείττων/κρείσσων","slug":"κρείττων/κρείσσων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϰρείττων</el>/<el>ϰρείσσων, ον</el>,</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ gen.\">gen.</a> <b><el>ονος</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Skt.\">Skt.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ assoc.\">assoc.</a>] functions as <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ comp.\">comp.</a> of <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀγαθός\">ἀγαθός</a></el> ‘having a degree of advantage’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> in status or rank <b>better, superior (to):</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a> <b><a href='B:650 1:4'>Hb 1:4</a>;</b> things <b><a href='B:530 12:31'>1 Cor 12:31</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a>; <a href='B:650 7:19'>Hb 7:19</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in Hb<b>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> of value <b>better, more advantageous <a href='B:530 7:9'>1 Cor 7:9</a>; <a href='B:530 11:17'>11:17</a>; <a href='B:570 1:23'>Phil 1:23</a>; <a href='B:650 6:9'>Hb 6:9</a>; <a href='B:670 3:17'>1 Pt 3:17</a>; <a href='B:680 2:21'>2 Pt 2:21</a>.</b> Nt. <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ acc.\">acc.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ sg.\">sg.</a> used as <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adv.\">adv.</a> <b><a href='B:530 7:38'>1 Cor 7:38</a>; <a href='B:650 12:24'>Hb 12:24</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:κρέας\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:κρέμαμαι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}